---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Executive Summary"
  description="Boing Network — Executive summary for investors and grant programs. Authentic L1 blockchain built from first principles with protocol-enforced quality assurance, sustainable tokenomics, and 100% transparency."
  canonical="/investors"
  pageClass="page-app"
>
  <article class="investor-page">
    <header class="investor-header">
      <img src="/logo.svg" alt="Boing Network" class="investor-logo" width="64" height="64" />
      <h1>Boing Network</h1>
      <p class="investor-tagline">Executive Summary</p>
      <p class="investor-subtitle">Authentic. Decentralized. Optimal. Quality-Assured.</p>
      <p class="investor-stage"><strong>Stage:</strong> MVP / Prototype · Testnet live · SDK & CLI ready</p>
    </header>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Vision</h2>
      <p>Boing Network is an <strong>authentic, decentralized L1 blockchain</strong> built from first principles — optimized for efficiency, independent of other chains, and committed to <strong>100% transparency</strong> and <strong>protocol-enforced quality assurance</strong>. We are building the infrastructure for a sustainable, scam-resistant DeFi ecosystem where only assets meeting defined security and compliance standards reach the chain.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>The Problem</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Scam proliferation</strong> — Most chains allow any bytecode; users and protocols bear the risk of malicious or low-quality deployments.</li>
        <li><strong>Network congestion</strong> — When anything and everything can be deployed, chains become clogged with low-value or spam transactions, driving up fees and degrading UX for legitimate users.</li>
        <li><strong>Fragmented liquidity</strong> — Value is spread across dozens of chains; cross-chain coordination is trust-heavy and complex.</li>
        <li><strong>Opaque governance</strong> — Many networks lack verifiable transparency in tokenomics, treasury, and upgrades.</li>
        <li><strong>Unsustainable incentives</strong> — Reward cliffs and unchecked inflation undermine long-term viability.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Our Solution</h2>
      <p>Boing introduces <strong>protocol-enforced quality assurance</strong> — the first L1 where only deployments meeting defined rules (bytecode, security heuristics, purpose declaration) are accepted. By ensuring that not anything and everything can be deployed to the chain, our built-in QA directly reduces network congestion: the mempool and blocks stay focused on legitimate, high-quality transactions instead of spam and low-value deployments. Automation handles known cases; a community QA pool handles edge cases. We combine this with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>QA at the infrastructure layer</strong> — Protocol-enforced filtering so only quality deployments reach the chain, reducing congestion from the start</li>
        <li><strong>Native account abstraction</strong> — Gasless UX, social recovery, session keys at the protocol level</li>
        <li><strong>Adaptive gas model</strong> — Dynamic pricing with predictable caps</li>
        <li><strong>Cross-chain DeFi coordination</strong> — Light client verification, unified liquidity routing via boing.finance</li>
        <li><strong>Phased governance</strong> — Time-locked proposals; no surprise upgrades</li>
        <li><strong>Sustainable tokenomics</strong> — Uncapped supply with floor-triggered waves; no reward cliffs</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Competitive Advantage</h2>
      <p>Most established L1s permit any bytecode deployment—quality checks, when they exist, live in applications or contracts, not consensus. <strong>Boing is the first L1 to enforce quality at the protocol layer.</strong> This is infrastructure, not a dApp feature. We reduce congestion and scam risk at the source.</p>
      <h3>Unique Differentiators</h3>
      <div class="differentiators-grid">
        <div class="diff-card">
          <span class="diff-icon">🔐</span>
          <h3>Protocol QA</h3>
          <p>Only quality assets on-chain. No other L1 enforces deployment standards at the protocol layer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <span class="diff-icon">📊</span>
          <h3>100% Transparency</h3>
          <p>Open design docs, public specs, auditable tokenomics. Trust through verification.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <span class="diff-icon">⚡</span>
          <h3>Rust + BFT</h3>
          <p>Custom VM, PoS + HotStuff BFT, libp2p networking. Built for security and performance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <span class="diff-icon">🌐</span>
          <h3>Ecosystem Ready</h3>
          <p>SDK, CLI, success-based dApp incentives, decentralized automation. Developer-first.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Technical Status</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Core protocol</strong> — Consensus (HotStuff), execution (custom VM), state (Sparse Merkle), P2P (libp2p)</li>
        <li><strong>Developer tools</strong> — <code>boing init</code>, <code>boing dev</code>, <code>boing deploy</code>; Boing SDK (TypeScript)</li>
        <li><strong>Protocol QA</strong> — Automated checks (opcode whitelist, blocklist, scam patterns); community pool for edge cases</li>
        <li><strong>Tokenomics</strong> — Emission curve, fee split, dApp incentive caps, floor-triggered waves</li>
        <li><strong>Testnet</strong> — Bootnodes, faucet, public RPC; VibeMiner one-click validator integration</li>
        <li><strong>Website & docs</strong> — boing.network; comprehensive technical documentation</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Target Market</h2>
      <p><strong>Primary:</strong> DeFi users, protocols, and validators seeking a scam-resistant L1 with transparent governance and sustainable incentives. <strong>Secondary:</strong> Developers building on a quality-assured chain.</p>
      <p>Global DeFi TVL exceeds $50B across hundreds of chains. Millions of users and thousands of protocols face scam and congestion risk daily. We target early adopters: security-conscious protocols, validators tired of opaque ecosystems, and users burned by scams. Long-term TAM: DeFi protocols requiring compliance or quality standards that cannot achieve that on permissionless-anything chains.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Go-to-Market</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Phase 1 — Testnet:</strong> Public bootnodes, faucet, RPC. Developer docs, CLI, SDK, VibeMiner one-click validator. Incentivized testnet (2–4 weeks) rewards validators, developers, and users.</li>
        <li><strong>Phase 2 — Mainnet:</strong> Security audits, formal verification. Validator bootstrap via early incentives and hardware grants (capped). Developer grants and hackathons. boing.finance integration for cross-chain swap, bridge, and liquidity routing.</li>
        <li><strong>Phase 3 — Ecosystem:</strong> Success-based dApp incentives with per-dApp caps; community QA pool; governance-driven evolution. Channels: GitHub, Discord, docs, accelerator/VC outreach.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Tokenomics & Value Creation</h2>
      <p><strong>Uncapped supply with floor-triggered waves.</strong> Initial supply fixed at mainnet launch. When circulating supply reaches a floor, new waves mint to restore balance.</p>
      <div class="tokenomics-breakdown">
        <div class="token-row"><span class="token-pct">55%</span> Staking Rewards</div>
        <div class="token-row"><span class="token-pct">30%</span> Treasury (grants, audits, ecosystem)</div>
        <div class="token-row"><span class="token-pct">15%</span> Community & Grants</div>
      </div>
      <p>Fee split: 70–80% to validators, 20–30% to treasury. At maturity, <strong>fee revenue dominates</strong>—validators and treasury earn from transactions; emissions decline (Year 1 ~8%, Year 10+ targets 1% floor or 0% if fees sufficient). dApp incentives (success-based, per-dApp capped) align developer success with adoption. Cross-chain DeFi via boing.finance captures value from swap fees and liquidity.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Validation</h2>
      <p><strong>Technical:</strong> Core protocol implemented—consensus (HotStuff), execution (custom VM), state (Sparse Merkle), P2P (libp2p). Node runs single- and multi-node. CLI and SDK scaffold and deploy dApps. Protocol QA design includes opcode whitelist, blocklist, scam patterns. Build and tests pass; fuzz harness for primitives.</p>
      <p><strong>Operational:</strong> Testnet infrastructure ready—bootnodes, faucet, public RPC. Documentation supports validators and developers. boing.network live with docs, faucet, investor materials.</p>
      <p><strong>Market:</strong> Design aligns with user pain (scams, congestion, opacity). Six-pillar philosophy and sustainable tokenomics documented. Incentivized testnet plan defined. Next: bootnode launch, public testnet, early validator/developer feedback.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section">
      <h2>Use of Funds</h2>
      <p>Grant and accelerator support would accelerate:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Mainnet launch</strong> — Security audits, formal verification, infrastructure hardening</li>
        <li><strong>Ecosystem growth</strong> — Developer grants, hackathons, SDK improvements</li>
        <li><strong>Validator bootstrap</strong> — Early validator incentives, hardware grants (capped)</li>
        <li><strong>Community & education</strong> — Documentation, tutorials, community programs</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section pitch-deck-section" id="pitch-deck">
      <h2>Pitch Deck</h2>
      <p class="deck-intro">Browse our investor deck below or <button type="button" class="btn-download-pdf" id="download-pdf">Save as PDF</button>.</p>
      <div class="pitch-deck">
        <div class="deck-slides" id="deck-slides">
          <div class="deck-slide active" data-slide="0">
            <h3>Boing Network</h3>
            <p class="slide-tagline">Authentic. Decentralized. Optimal. Quality-Assured.</p>
            <p class="slide-stage">MVP · Testnet Live · SDK & CLI Ready</p>
            <p class="slide-sub">Executive Summary for Investors</p>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="1">
            <h3>The Problem</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Scam proliferation — users bear risk</li>
              <li>Network congestion from low-value deployments</li>
              <li>Fragmented liquidity across chains</li>
              <li>Opaque governance</li>
              <li>Unsustainable incentives</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="2">
            <h3>Our Solution</h3>
            <p>Protocol-enforced quality assurance — only quality deployments reach the chain.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>QA at infrastructure layer</li>
              <li>Native account abstraction</li>
              <li>Adaptive gas model</li>
              <li>Cross-chain DeFi coordination</li>
              <li>Sustainable tokenomics</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="3">
            <h3>Competitive Advantage</h3>
            <p>No other L1 enforces deployment standards at the protocol layer.</p>
            <p>Protocol QA · 100% Transparency · Rust + BFT · boing.finance integration</p>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="4">
            <h3>Target Market</h3>
            <p>DeFi users, protocols, validators seeking scam-resistant L1. Global DeFi TVL &gt;$50B. We target security-conscious protocols, validators, and users burned by scams.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="5">
            <h3>Go-to-Market</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Phase 1: Testnet, incentivized program</li>
              <li>Phase 2: Mainnet, audits, boing.finance</li>
              <li>Phase 3: Ecosystem, dApp incentives</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="6">
            <h3>Tokenomics & Value</h3>
            <p><strong>55%</strong> Staking · <strong>30%</strong> Treasury · <strong>15%</strong> Community & Grants</p>
            <p>Fee revenue dominates at maturity. No reward cliffs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="7">
            <h3>Validation</h3>
            <p>Technical: Core protocol live. Operational: Testnet infra ready. Market: Design aligns with user pain; incentivized testnet plan defined.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="8">
            <h3>Use of Funds</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Mainnet launch — audits, infrastructure</li>
              <li>Ecosystem growth — grants, hackathons</li>
              <li>Validator bootstrap</li>
              <li>Community & education</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="deck-slide" data-slide="9">
            <h3>Get in Touch</h3>
            <p><a href="https://github.com/chiku524/boing.network" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a> · <a href="https://boing.network">Website</a> · <a href="/community">Community</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="deck-nav">
          <button type="button" class="deck-btn deck-prev" id="deck-prev" aria-label="Previous slide">← Prev</button>
          <span class="deck-dots" id="deck-dots" role="tablist"></span>
          <button type="button" class="deck-btn deck-next" id="deck-next" aria-label="Next slide">Next →</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="investor-section investor-cta">
      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>Interested in grants, accelerator programs, or partnerships?</p>
      <p class="contact-links">
        <a href="https://github.com/chiku524/boing.network" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a> ·
        <a href="https://boing.network">Website</a> ·
        <a href="/community">Community</a>
      </p>
      <p class="contact-note">We are open to direct outreach — reach out via our GitHub or community channels.</p>
    </section>

    <footer class="investor-footer">
      <p>Boing Network — Authentic. Decentralized. Optimal. Quality-Assured.</p>
      <p><a href="/">← Return to Home</a></p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Page header (investor-header) must not be sticky — override global header rule */
  .investor-header {
    position: static;
  }
  .investor-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
  }
  .investor-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.2);
  }
  .investor-logo {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .investor-page h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }
  .investor-tagline {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--network-primary-light);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .investor-subtitle {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .investor-stage {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.15);
    border: 1px solid rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.3);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .investor-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .investor-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: var(--network-primary-light);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .investor-section h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .investor-section p,
  .investor-section li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .investor-section ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0.75rem 0;
  }
  .investor-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .investor-section code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.15);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .differentiators-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .diff-card {
    background: rgba(18, 24, 41, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.2);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  }
  .diff-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.4);
  }
  .diff-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .diff-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .tokenomics-breakdown {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .token-row {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .token-pct {
    display: inline-block;
    min-width: 3ch;
    color: var(--network-cyan);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .investor-cta {
    background: rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.25);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .contact-links {
    margin: 1rem 0 !important;
  }
  .contact-links a {
    color: var(--network-cyan);
  }
  .contact-links a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .contact-note {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted) !important;
  }
  .investor-footer {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.2);
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .investor-footer a {
    color: var(--network-primary-light);
  }
  .investor-footer a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Pitch deck */
  .pitch-deck-section {
    background: rgba(18, 24, 41, 0.5);
    border: 1px solid rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.25);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .deck-intro {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem !important;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem 1rem;
  }
  .btn-download-pdf {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-teal), var(--accent-cyan));
    color: var(--bg-primary);
    border: none;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: inherit;
  }
  .btn-download-pdf:hover {
    filter: brightness(1.1);
  }
  .pitch-deck {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .deck-slides {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 280px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .deck-slide {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    padding: 2rem;
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
  }
  .deck-slide.active {
    display: flex;
    opacity: 1;
    position: relative;
  }
  .deck-slide h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem !important;
    margin-bottom: 1rem !important;
    color: var(--accent-teal) !important;
  }
  .deck-slide ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0 1rem !important;
    padding: 0 !important;
  }
  .deck-slide li {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem !important;
  }
  .slide-tagline {
    font-size: 1.2rem !important;
    color: var(--text-primary) !important;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem !important;
  }
  .slide-stage {
    color: var(--accent-teal) !important;
    font-size: 0.9rem !important;
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0.5rem !important;
  }
  .slide-sub {
    color: var(--text-tertiary) !important;
    font-size: 0.95rem !important;
  }
  .deck-nav {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .deck-btn {
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .deck-btn:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-teal);
    color: var(--accent-teal);
  }
  .deck-dots {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .deck-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--border-color);
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .deck-dot.active {
    background: var(--accent-teal);
  }
  .deck-dot:hover {
    background: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  /* Pitch deck responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .pitch-deck-section {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    }
    .deck-slide {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    }
    .deck-slide h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem !important;
    }
    .deck-nav {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .investor-page {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    }
    .investor-page h1 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
    .differentiators-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .tokenomics-breakdown {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .investor-page {
      padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
    }
    .investor-header {
      padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .investor-section {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 375px) {
    .investor-page {
      padding: 1rem 0.75rem;
    }
    .investor-cta {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    }
  }

  /* Print & PDF */
  @media print {
    .investor-page {
      max-width: 100%;
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }
    .investor-header {
      break-after: avoid;
    }
    .investor-section {
      break-inside: avoid;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .differentiators-grid {
      display: grid !important;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr) !important;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .diff-card {
      break-inside: avoid;
      background: #f9fafb !important;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb !important;
      -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
      print-color-adjust: exact;
    }
    .investor-cta {
      break-inside: avoid;
      background: #f3f4f6 !important;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb !important;
    }
    .investor-footer {
      break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .investor-section p,
    .investor-section li {
      color: #374151 !important;
    }
    .investor-section h2 {
      color: #4f46e5 !important;
    }
    .pitch-deck-section {
      break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .deck-nav {
      display: none;
    }
    .deck-slides {
      min-height: auto;
    }
    .deck-slide {
      position: relative !important;
      display: block !important;
      opacity: 1 !important;
      break-inside: avoid;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      padding: 1rem !important;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    }
    .deck-slide:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  (function () {
    const slides = document.querySelectorAll('.deck-slide');
    const prevBtn = document.getElementById('deck-prev');
    const nextBtn = document.getElementById('deck-next');
    const dotsEl = document.getElementById('deck-dots');
    const downloadBtn = document.getElementById('download-pdf');
    if (slides.length === 0) return;

    let current = 0;
    const total = slides.length;

    function goTo(i) {
      current = (i + total) % total;
      slides.forEach((s, j) => s.classList.toggle('active', j === current));
      dotsEl?.querySelectorAll('.deck-dot').forEach((d, j) => d.classList.toggle('active', j === current));
    }

    prevBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => goTo(current - 1));
    nextBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => goTo(current + 1));

    slides.forEach((_, i) => {
      const dot = document.createElement('button');
      dot.type = 'button';
      dot.className = 'deck-dot' + (i === 0 ? ' active' : '');
      dot.setAttribute('aria-label', `Slide ${i + 1}`);
      dot.addEventListener('click', () => goTo(i));
      dotsEl?.appendChild(dot);
    });

    downloadBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => window.print());

    document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') goTo(current - 1);
      if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') goTo(current + 1);
    });
  })();
</script>
